        "A **fuel** is a substance burned to release energy. Most fuels (petrol, methane, wood) contain carbon and hydrogen. When they burn there are two possibilities depending on how much oxygen is available.\n\n**Complete combustion** happens with **plenty of oxygen**. The carbon becomes **carbon dioxide** and the hydrogen becomes **water**, releasing the most energy with a clean blue flame:\n\n- methane + oxygen → carbon dioxide + water\n\n**Incomplete combustion** happens when oxygen is **limited**. It releases less energy and produces:\n\n- **carbon monoxide** (CO), a toxic, colourless, odourless gas that stops blood carrying oxygen\n- **soot** (tiny carbon particles) and a smoky yellow flame\n\nThis is why faulty gas heaters and blocked chimneys are dangerous — they cause incomplete combustion and deadly carbon monoxide. Carbon monoxide alarms exist for exactly this reason.",
      diagram:
        `<svg viewBox="0 0 320 150" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" role="img" aria-label="Complete combustion gives carbon dioxide and water with a blue flame; incomplete gives carbon monoxide and soot with a yellow flame"><rect x="10" y="14" width="140" height="124" rx="8" fill="#eff6ff" stroke="#2563eb"/><text x="80" y="32" font-size="10" text-anchor="middle" fill="#1e3a8a">COMPLETE</text><path d="M80 44 q-12 14 0 28 q12 -14 0 -28 z" fill="#3b82f6" stroke="#1d4ed8"/><text x="80" y="92" font-size="8" text-anchor="middle" fill="#1e3a8a">plenty of O&#8322;</text><text x="80" y="106" font-size="8" text-anchor="middle" fill="#1e3a8a">&#8594; CO&#8322; + water</text><text x="80" y="120" font-size="8" text-anchor="middle" fill="#1e3a8a">blue flame, most energy</text><rect x="170" y="14" width="140" height="124" rx="8" fill="#fffbeb" stroke="#d97706"/><text x="240" y="32" font-size="10" text-anchor="middle" fill="#92400e">INCOMPLETE</text><path d="M240 44 q-12 16 0 30 q12 -16 0 -30 z" fill="#facc15" stroke="#ca8a04"/><circle cx="232" cy="42" r="2" fill="#3f3f46"/><circle cx="248" cy="40" r="2" fill="#3f3f46"/><text x="240" y="92" font-size="8" text-anchor="middle" fill="#92400e">limited O&#8322;</text><text x="240" y="106" font-size="8" text-anchor="middle" fill="#92400e">&#8594; CO + soot + water</text><text x="240" y="120" font-size="8" text-anchor="middle" fill="#92400e">yellow flame, less energy</text></svg>`,
      diagramCaption:
        "Plenty of oxygen → clean blue flame, CO₂ and water. Limited oxygen → smoky yellow flame, toxic carbon monoxide and soot.",
      keyPoints: [
        "Complete combustion (lots of O₂) → carbon dioxide + water, blue flame, most energy.",
        "Incomplete combustion (little O₂) → carbon monoxide + soot, yellow flame, less energy.",
        "Carbon monoxide is toxic because it stops blood carrying oxygen.",
      ],
